-- Actuaries Probed Over Equitable Life Won’t Face Discipline
-- B y   J i m   S i l v e r
-- 2012-08-17T20:38:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-17/actuaries-probed-over-equitable-life-won-t-face-discipline.html
U.K. government and Ernst & Young
actuaries who failed to stop Equitable Life Assurance Society
from offering generous annuity rates that led to its near-
collapse in 2000 won’t face disciplinary action.  A review of their actions found “there is no realistic
prospect that a tribunal would make an adverse finding” against
the actuaries, the U.K.’s Accounting and Actuarial Discipline
Board said today in a  statement  on its website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jim Silver in  New York  at 
 jsilver@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
